2 (d) (1) If 140 or more days of live racing in a year are held at Laurel Race
3 Course, the Comptroller shall pay:
4 (i) for each day of live racing, $2,000 to Anne Arundel County, $500
5 to Howard County, and $300 to the City of Laurel; and
6 (ii) for each additional day of intertrack betting without live racing
7 held, $1,000 to Anne Arundel County, $250 to Howard County, and $150 to the City of
8 Laurel.
9 (2) If fewer than 140 days of live racing in a year are held at Laurel Race
10 Course, the Comptroller shall pay:
11 (i) for each day of live racing or each day of intertrack betting
12 without live racing held, up to a maximum payment for 140 days, $2,000 to Anne Arundel
13 County, $500 to Howard County, and $300 to the City of Laurel; and
14 (ii) for each additional day of intertrack betting without live racing
15 held, $1,000 to Anne Arundel County, $250 to Howard County, and $150 to the City of
16 Laurel.
